    "created_at": "2016-01-04T18:18:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-04T18:18:19Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "First, it looks like that grpc build actually succeeded. The message at the end is just a warning, and does not actually affect the Ruby library.\n\nSecond, you are installing the grpc core, so setting `GRPC_ROOT` is not only unnecessary, but actively harmful. You should instead set `PKG_CONFIG_PATH=\"$PKG_CONFIG_PATH:$HOME/grpc_build/lib/pkgconfig\"`.\n\nWhen you set `GRPC_ROOT` to a grpc clone _and_ `pkg-config` does not find the existing grpc installation (which it would not do by default because of the custom install location), the Ruby library links against `$GRPC_ROOT/libs/opt/libgrpc`. Because you already ran `make`, it links with `libgrpc.so`. Then, when you try to run it, it cannot find `libgrpc.so` in the default shared library search path.\n\nAs ctiller mentioned, we will eliminate this problem in the next release (0.12)\n"
  },
